r\n             \r\n         \r\n         \r\n             \r\n                 Job Description \r\n             \r\n             Safety Specialist I Location Anchorage, AK, US Organization Name ASRC Energy Services Department Description  Brief Description   The Health, Safety, and Environmental, and Training (HSET) Safety Specialist I is an entry-level position responsible for monitoring regulatory compliance and the maintenance of a safe work environment for all personnel, subcontractors, and customers involved in Company operations.   Detailed Description    Prepare and maintain documentation to ensure compliance with federal and state laws, regulations, and Company requirements.    Provide regulatory compliance information to HSET personnel, subcontractors, and customers.    Assist department personnel with HSET case management, job safety analysis (JSA), and job hazard analysis (JHA) reports.    Assist department personnel with facility inspections of Company-controlled buildings and facilities.    Use root cause analysis systems to identify HSET risks and develop methods for maintaining a safe work environment.    Assist department personnel with investigations, interviews, photographing, and documentation.    Assist department personnel with industrial hygiene field monitoring including hot work, unit work, and confined space entry permitting.    Maintain basic understanding of Alaska Workers Compensation Law.    Comply with Company and customer policies and procedures .    Support AES zero-incident safety culture and assume personal accountability and responsibility for safe work practices in all projects, activities, and operations.    Job Requirements   Minimum Education and Experience    Associate degree in a safety-related field with a minimum of two years of safety experience preferred. A combination of five years education, HSET training, and craft experience may be considered in lieu of an associate degree. Thorough knowledge of OSHA 29 CFR 1904, 1910, and 1926, and a basic understanding of NFPA, NIOSH, ASME, and ANSI required. Proficiency with Microsoft Office required.    Certifications    Occupational Health and Safety Technician (OHST) or Construction, Health, and Safety Technician (CHST) certification must be obtained within one year from date of hire. Certifications are tracked by the HSET Manager. North Slope Training Cooperative (NSTC) safety training certification required.   Additional Details    A candidate must be able to meet the following non-exclusive requirements:    1. Meet the AES Driver Licenses and Records Policy     2. Take and pass a pre-employment drug test which may include both UA and hair testing.    3. Meet the physical requirements of this position including working in a remote location under arctic conditions.    The availability of this position is contingent upon the Companys continued operational needs once training is completed \r\n         \r\n         \r\n             \r\n                 To Apply: \r\n             \r\n             Sign In    Register \r\n\r\n         \r\n         \r\n         \r\n         \r\n     \r\n \r\n \r\n      \r\n     \r\n         \r\n             \r\n                 \r\n                     Welcome to iHireEnvironmental! \r\n                     Safety Specialist I \r\n                     \r\n                              Arctic Slope Regional Corporation  \r\n                           &nbsp;Anchorage, AK \r\n                     \r\n                     \r\n                         Job Description: \r\n                     \r\n                     \r\n                         \r\n                             \r\n                                Safety Specialist I Location Anchorage, AK, US Organization Name ASRC Energy Services Department Description  Brief Description   The Health, Safety, and Environmental, and Training (HSET) Safety Specialist I is an entry-level position responsible for monitoring regulatory compliance and the maintenance of 